  "prompt": "What are some less fictioned movie everyone must watch?",
  "response": "If you're looking for movies that are more rooted in reality or based on true events, here\u2019s a list of **less fictionalized films** that are highly regarded and worth watching:\n\n### **Based on True Stories**\n1. **Schindler\u2019s List** (1993) - The story of Oskar Schindler, who saved over a thousand Jewish lives during the Holocaust.\n2. **The Pursuit of Happyness** (2006) - The inspiring true story of Chris Gardner\u2019s journey from homelessness to success.\n3. **Spotlight** (2015) - A gripping tale of investigative journalism uncovering the Catholic Church\u2019s child abuse scandal.\n4. **The Social Network** (2010) - The creation of Facebook and the legal battles that followed.\n5. **Hidden Figures** (2016) - The untold story of Black women mathematicians at NASA during the Space Race.\n6. **Catch Me If You Can** (2002) - The true story of Frank Abagnale Jr., a masterful con artist.\n7. **12 Years a Slave** (2013) - A harrowing account of Solomon Northup\u2019s experience as a free man sold into slavery.\n\n### **Historical Dramas**\n8. **A Beautiful Mind** (2001) - The life of mathematician John Nash and his struggle with schizophrenia.\n9. **The King\u2019s Speech** (2010) - King George VI\u2019s journey to overcome his stutter with the help of a speech therapist.\n10. **Lincoln** (2012) - A portrayal of Abraham Lincoln\u2019s fight to pass the 13th Amendment.\n\n### **War Films**\n11. **Saving Private Ryan** (1998) - A fictional story but grounded in the realities of World War II.\n12. **Hacksaw Ridge** (2016) - The true story of Desmond Doss, a conscientious objector who saved lives during WWII.\n13. **Dunkirk** (2017) - A tense depiction of the Dunkirk evacuation during WWII.\n\n### **Social and Political Stories**\n14. **Hotel Rwanda** (2004) - The story of Paul Rusesabagina, who saved lives during the Rwandan genocide.\n15. **Selma** (2014) - A powerful depiction of Martin Luther King Jr.\u2019s fight for voting rights.\n16. **The Big Short** (2015) - The 2008 financial crisis explained through the stories of those who bet against the housing market.\n\n### **Crime and Justice**\n17. **The Insider** (1999) - A whistleblower\u2019s fight against the tobacco industry.\n18. **Erin Brockovich** (2000) - The true story of a legal clerk who exposed environmental pollution.\n19. **Zodiac** (2007) - The hunt for the Zodiac Killer in the 1960s and 1970s.\n\n### **Human Interest**\n20. **The Pursuit of Happyness** (2006) - Already mentioned, but worth repeating for its emotional impact.\n21. **The Blind Side** (2009) - The true story of Michael Oher, an NFL player who overcame adversity.\n22. **Wild** (2014) - Cheryl Strayed\u2019s solo hike along the Pacific Crest Trail as a form of healing.\n\nThese films not only entertain but also educate, inspire, and shed light on important historical events, personal struggles, and societal issues.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
